## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Write a new unit test class in `backend/payments/tests.py`:
  - `test_unenrolled_student_cannot_view_secure_lesson_fields`: Verify that accessing lesson detail lists without enrollment filters out `video_url`, `body_text`, `file_attachment`, and `quiz_questions`.
  - `test_enroll_in_paid_course`: Verify that a paid course enrollment fails without a transaction ID, and succeeds and creates a `Payment` object when provided.
  - `test_progress_triggers_certificate_generation`: Verify that when progress hits 100%, a `Certificate` instance is generated with a valid `.pdf` file.

### Manual Verification
- Log in as a student. Explore the catalog and view a course syllabus. Verify that video URLs / text are not visible or fetched in network tabs.
- Enroll in a free course, complete all lessons, verify that the progress updates to 100%, and check that the certificate downloads as a professional PDF.
- Enroll in a paid course, click "Buy & Enroll", enter mock details, check that it redirects successfully to the classroom.
